cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.NE 

This paper is about Bayesian optimization of expensive black-box objective functions, which is a common problem in machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses applications in rocket science and robotics, which suggests that cs.SY (Systems and Control) may be a relevant sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves parallel computation, which could fall under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
